      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">In the midst of a busy day at a large tertiary hospital in Uttar Pradesh, the nurse supervisor, Mrs. Gupta, is preparing a checklist for waste management training for new nurses. While listing down the different types of biomedical waste and their appropriate methods of disposal, she recalls that there&#39;s a specific type of waste that is typically NOT autoclaved before final disposal. Which of the following types of waste is Mrs. Gupta thinking about?</span></span></p>",
