      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. B. Biohazard</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Explanation:</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>THE BIOHAZARD SYMBOL:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">An <strong>image</strong> that <strong>warns</strong> people of possible <strong>exposure </strong>to <strong>biological substances</strong> that are <strong>harmful </strong>to <strong>living organisms</strong>.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">These <strong>biohazards</strong> can be <strong>viruses, toxins</strong> or <strong>medical waste</strong>.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Symbol </strong>was created by <strong>Charles Baldwin</strong> in <strong>1966.</strong></span></li></ul><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Educational Objective:</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/Picture1_fCtJkID.png\" width=\"2760\" height=\"1674\"></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Reference: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg. 888</strong></span></p>",
